This paper deals with the problem of domain adaptation and zero-shot learning in computer vision, which is a subfield of computer science that falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also uses machine learning techniques such as supervised locality preserving projection (SLPP), which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as zero-shot learning, which falls under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper deals with multimedia processing, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
